---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Portrait from '../components/Portrait.astro';
import SocialLinks from '../components/SocialLinks.astro';
import { patents } from '../data/patents';

const facts: [string, string][] = [
  ['Working in cloud', '10+ years'],
  ['Largest program', '25,000+ AWS accounts · 13M+ assets'],
];
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Matthew Gladney - cloud and AI security engineering leader building identity-centric security at massive scale."
>
  <div class="container" style="padding-top:64px">
    <section class="about-intro">
      <div class="about-intro__text">
        <span class="label">About</span>
        <h1 class="display">Identity-centric security, at massive scale.</h1>
        <p class="prose-p" style="color:var(--fg-1);max-width:540px">
          A cloud and AI security engineering leader - and a 2x acquisition survivor.
        </p>
        <div class="about-socials"><SocialLinks display="icon-label" /></div>
      </div>
      <Portrait class="about-intro__portrait" />
    </section>

    <section class="measure" style="margin-top:48px">
      <p class="prose-p" style="color:var(--fg-1);margin-bottom:18px">
        Most days, I take on the security problems that don’t have an answer yet - first it was
        cloud at the scale that broke a lot of vendors, and now defining how AI agents should work
        securely. To me, the through-line is the same: a workload may eventually do something you
        didn’t intend, and we have to design a security posture that anticipates and mitigates the
        potential for impact. I also believe great security accelerates rather than blocks
        innovation.
      </p>
      <p class="prose-p" style="color:var(--fg-1);margin-bottom:18px">
        Agents are where more of my work is now - securing them, building them to do security work,
        and building the benchmarks that make sure they’re both secure and effective at their jobs -
        then leveling up other teams to do the same.
      </p>
      <p class="prose-p" style="color:var(--fg-1)">
        With over a decade of cloud experience across complex environments scaling to 25,000+ AWS
        accounts and 13M+ assets, I’ve delivered on both sides of the line: architecting and
        delivering the CIEM and CMDB products we sold to customers, and building out security
        ecosystems on internal teams when no product fit. Along the way I authored two cloud-related
        patents.
      </p>
      <p class="small" style="margin-top:14px">
        {
          patents.map((pt, i) => (
            <>
              {i > 0 && <span class="faint"> · </span>}
              <a
                href={pt.href}
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                style="font-family:var(--font-mono);font-size:13px"
              >
                {pt.id} →
              </a>
            </>
          ))
        }
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="facts">
      {
        facts.map(([k, v]) => (
          <div class="fact">
            <span class="small muted">{k}</span>
            <span class="body fact__value">{v}</span>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </section>

    <section class="measure" style="margin-top:8px">
      <span class="label" style="display:block;margin-bottom:10px">Currently</span>
      <p class="prose-p" style="color:var(--fg-1)">
        I help organize <a href="https://fwdcloudsec.org/">fwd:cloudsec North America</a> and sit on the
        <a href="https://www.cve.org/ProgramOrganization/WorkingGroups">CVE AI Working Group</a>.
        Open to additional advisory, board, and committee work where that’s useful.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
